import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.hist(data['fertility'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(data['fertility'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    ax.axvline(data['fertility'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    ax.set_xlabel('Fertility')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of fertility across all countries?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['fertility', 'life_expect']]
    plt.scatter(data['fertility'], data['life_expect'], alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Fertility')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between fertility and life expectancy?', wrap=True)
    plt.axvline(data['fertility'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', label=f'Median Fertility: {data["fertility"].median():.2f}')
    plt.axhline(data['life_expect'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', label=f'Median Life Expectancy: {data["life_expect"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='fertility', ascending=False).head(10)
    plt.bar(data['country'], data['fertility'], color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=data['fertility'].max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Max fertility: {data['fertility'].max():.2f}")
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('Country')
    plt.ylabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.title('What are the top 10 countries with the highest fertility rates?')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['n_fertility', 'fertility'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['year'], data['n_fertility'], label='Normalized Fertility Rate')
    ax.plot(data['year'], data['fertility'], label='Actual Fertility Rate')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Fertility Rate')
    ax.set_title('How does the normalized fertility rate compare to the actual fertility rate?', wrap=True)
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
